&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, March 22 (KCNA) -- The south headquarters of the national alliance for the country's reunification reportedly issued a statement titled "Let us remove dark clouds of war hanging above the Korean Peninsula by implementing the June 15 joint declaration" on March 15.
 The statement said that the large-scale joint military exercises staged across South Korea from March 21 are very hostile and offensive drills based on the "5027-98" operation plan designed to occupy the whole area of the north. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The preceding South Korea-U.S. joint military exercises regarding the north as the "enemy" had always stood in the way of the progress of the south-north relations, the statement noted: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It demanded an immediate stop to the joint military exercises that threaten peace on the Korean Peninsula and incite a show-down between the fellow countrymen. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. should honestly implement the agreement with the north and promptly renounce all the hostile policies toward the north and war scenarios, it noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It demanded the South Korean authorities honestly implement the June 15 joint declaration, a promise of reconciliation, reunification and peace that was agreed between Koreans.

Signal success in mushroom cultivation 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 22 (KCNA) -- Ri Son A, 48, well-known expert on the cultivation of mushroom, recently succeeded in the mass-cultivation of phellinus linteus berk proved to have a strong anti-cancer effect, its cancer-resisting rate being 96.7 , and an apparent immunity revitalizing effect.
 She works as a room chief of the Rungra science and technology centre of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After graduating from the biology faculty of Kim Il Sung University in Juche 67 (1978) she succeeded in the cultivation of a tobacco somatic hybrid breed by way of cell engineering in 1985, causing a great sensation at home. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She established and put into practice the method of artificial cultivation of at least 50 varieties of mushrooms proved to be good for the health and longevity of people including sweet armillaria, ganoderma mushroom and agaricus bisporus. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She succeeded in developing "spawn of natural material" that overcame the shortcomings of cereal spawn in 1993, thus opening a prospect of mass-producing various edible mushrooms at cheap cost. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The "spawn of natural material" won a gold medal at the 24th geneva international exhibition of inventions, new technologies and products. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ri is also a pioneer in studying "the science of mushroom cultivation" in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She is an author of books "cultivation of mushroom," "collection of mushrooms" and "production of mushroom spawn and its cultivation" and scores of scientific papers and technical manuals. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She was awarded the degree of doctor of biology in 1995 and the title of merited scientist in 1996.

"Comet" of Women's football 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, March 22 (KCNA) -- During the 3rd women's world cup tournament in 1999 the then chief coach of the American team predicted that Jin Pyol Hui, a member of the DPRK women's football team who was known for her remarkable shooting ability, would threaten the goalkeepers of the world's top-seeded teams.
 Jin, who started her career in the Wolmido team, was already recognized as a star when she made her debut in the tournament soon after being selected for national team. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She played a key role in the 3-1 victory over Denmark at the group stage and caused serious threats for the Nigerian and American defences in subsequent matches. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A series of international events, including the Asian women's football championships, offered her a good opportunity to learn and improve her skill. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the 13th Asian tournament held in Chinese Taipei in December 2001, she showed her ability to the full. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During the game against china, the holders of the Asian title since 1986 and a team which had a number of versatile, quality players, she scored three times, stunning spectators and coaches alike. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Her inventiveness combined with bewildering speed and quickness of decision won the admiration of the crowds. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Jin, who is said to have appeared like a "comet" in the women's football world, sets herself apart from ordinary players with her explosive speed, superb dribbling skills and determination, acquired through intensive training. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Introspective and calm by nature, she imposes strict demands on herself in training. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In praise of her ability to read the game, excellent positional sense and incisive attacks, people say: "She's like a wild hawk suddenly flying down to seize a prey. Jin is now 22, and her ambitious target is to lift the world cup and become one of the world's top strikers."

Performance "Arirang" praised
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 22 (KCNA) -- Foreigners were deeply impressed to watch the all-round rehearsal of the mass gymnastic and artistic performance "Arirang".
 Nigel Baker, director of content of the London bureau of the Associated Press Television News, said that all scenes of the performance were wonderful, adding that it is hard to enjoy such show elsewhere. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is something unbelievable that human beings can provide such huge and beautiful background scenes, he noted, calling on the people of all countries to come and see the performance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Greg o'connor, head of an Australian group to study "Arirang," said that he has seen not a few gymnastic displays but this is the first time for him to see such a mass gymnastic and artistic performance and he would make positive efforts to let many people of Britain, France, Australia and other countries watch the performance "Arirang". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Sosnovskaya Irina, general manager of the Shambhala Travel Agency of Russia, said that the performance "Arirang" would prove to be peculiar and wonderful and her agency would make positive efforts to help more people enjoy the performance.

Youth league conference closes
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 22 (KCNA) -- The conference of the  Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League closed today after successfully winding up its work.
 At the second-day session Kim Kyong Ho, first secretary of the central committee of the league, made a report on the second agenda item "On adopting rules of the Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is stipulated in the new rules that the Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League is the youth league of President Kim Il Sung, the founder of the Korean youth movement, and its mission is to carry forward the revolutionary cause of Juche generation after generation and accomplish it, guided by the Juche idea, the president's revolutionary idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It also defines the youth league as a political reserve force of the Workers' Party of Korea and the young vanguard which takes the lead in devotedly safeguarding the leader of revolution, upholding the WPK's army-based revolutionary leadership with loyalty. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter called for thoroughly abiding by the new rules in the building and activities of the league. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made on the second agenda item. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The rules of the league were adopted with a unanimous approval at the conference. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Led by Kim Kyong Ho, all the participants in the conference took an oath of loyalty to leader Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The conference demonstrated the young vanguard's unshakable faith and revolutionary enthusiasm to hold Kim Il Sung in high esteem as the sun of Juche for all ages and carry to completion the revolutionary cause of Juche generation after generation under the army-based leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, a march of the participants in the conference and youth and students in Pyongyang took place at Kim Il Sung Square this day to renew their pledge.

DPRK ready to hold talks with Japan Red Cross Society
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, March 22 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the central committee of the Red Cross Society of the DPRK issued a statement on March 22 as regards much fuss made in Japan over the issue of "kidnapping".
 The statement said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There is much fuss in Japan these days after a "testimony" was made that a woman called Keiko Arimoto was "kidnapped" in 1983. But the DPRK has neither "allured" nor "kidnapped" her. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nevertheless, the DPRK decided to continue the investigation into "those missing". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The central committee of the DPRK Red Cross Society clarifies the stand that it is ready to hold talks with the Japan Red Cross Society on the issue of mutual concern at a convenient time.
